# .trufflehogignore â€” Paths and patterns that are known false positives for TruffleHog
#
# Trade-off documentation:
# TruffleHog without --only-verified catches more secrets (including unverified/high-entropy
# strings) but generates false positives on config files, docs, and test fixtures.
# This file mitigates false positives. Gitleaks with custom pattern rules provides the
# authoritative verdict; TruffleHog is defense-in-depth.
#
# Format: glob patterns, one per line
# Syntax: https://github.com/trufflesecurity/trufflehog#gitignore-syntax

# Example files and documentation
.env.example
docs/
*.md

# Audit sample log contains realistic (but fake) event data
audit/sample-audit.log

# Test fixtures
tests/
**/fixtures/
**/test_*
*_test.py

# AWS example credentials (well-known test values)
aws/oidc-setup.md

# Gitleaks config contains allowlist patterns that look like secrets
.gitleaks.toml

# Vault init script uses placeholder values
vault/init/vault-init.sh
